FBIS3-8236 "dreeu044_s_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 SLOVENIA Russia's Zhirinovskiy Held at Ljubljana Airport LD0703103494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 0943 GMT 7 Mar 94 LD0703103494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Ljubljana, 7 Mar (TANJUG) -- The leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, who, it has been learned, arrived in Slovenia this morning, has been held at Ljubljana's Brnik airport. Slovene authorities are not allowing Zhirinovskiy to enter the country although the leader of the Russian Liberal Democrats has a valid diplomatic passport of the Russian Federation. It is not clear whether the Slovene authorities will deny Zhirinovskiy entry, or whether they will let him stay, as is claimed, for a private visit to Slovenia.
